President Biden delivered a speech at Cuyahoga Community College in Cleveland, Ohio, discussing the progress made in the country's recovery from the COVID-19 pandemic and his plans for future economic growth. He highlighted the success of the vaccine rollout and the decline in COVID-19 cases and deaths. He emphasized the need to rebuild the economy from the bottom up and the middle out, rather than relying on trickle-down economics. Biden outlined his proposed investments in infrastructure, education, and research and development, emphasizing the importance of creating good-paying jobs and ensuring that all Americans have access to opportunities. He also called for raising the minimum wage to $15 per hour and passing the PRO Act to protect workers' rights to organize. Biden concluded by stating that the United States has the opportunity to win the future by making these investments and bringing everyone along.